									<article class="box post">
										<header>
											<h2>Computational biology research at the <strong><a href="https://www.biostat.wisc.edu/">University of Wisconsin-Madison</a></strong> and the <strong><a href="http://morgridge.org/">Morgridge Institute for Research</a></strong></h2>
										</header>
										<p>Our lab's research involves designing algorithms that leverage biological networks to connect different types of experimental data and detect surprising relationships among them.  We use such techniques to study human disease, in particular cancer and viral infection.  We also focus on the dynamic behaviors of biological networks and develop techniques to reconstruct dynamic models of signaling pathways and transcriptional regulatory networks from high-throughput proteomic and transcriptomic data.
										In addition, we use machine learning to prioritize biological experiments for drug discovery, protein engineering, and other biomedical challenges.</p>
										<ul class="actions">
											<li><a href="research.html" class="button icon fa-sitemap">Learn More</a></li>
										</ul>
									</article>

									<article class="box post">
										<header>
											<h2>Openings</h2>
										</header>
										<p>We are not currently actively recruiting new graduate students or postdocs.
										However, prospective graduate students are always welcome to contact Anthony to discuss research in case that changes.
										Please send a follow up message if you do not hear back after a week or two.</p>

										<p>Anthony is a potential academic co-advisor for the <a href="https://www.futurehouse.org/fellowship">FutureHouse 2026 AI-for-Science Independent Postdoctoral Fellowship Program</a>.</p>
									</article>

									<article class="box post">
										<header>
											<h2>Teaching</h2>
										</header>
										<p>In the Spring 2026 semester Anthony taught Ethics for Data Scientists.</p>
										<p>In the Fall 2019, 2021, 2022, 2023, 2024, and 2025 semesters Anthony co-taught Computational Network Biology with <a href="https://roylab.discovery.wisc.edu/">Sushmita Roy</a>.</p>
										<ul class="actions">
											<li><a href="https://bmi775.sites.wisc.edu/" class="button icon fa-book">2025 Website</a>
											<a href="https://bmi775.sites.wisc.edu/archives/fall-2024/" class="button icon fa-book">2024 Website</a>
											<a href="https://bmi775.sites.wisc.edu/archives/fall-2023/" class="button icon fa-book">2023 Website</a>
											<a href="https://bmi775.sites.wisc.edu/archives/fall-2022/" class="button icon fa-book">2022 Website</a>
											<a href="https://bmi775.sites.wisc.edu/archives/fall-2021/" class="button icon fa-book">2021 Website</a>
											<a href="https://bmi775.sites.wisc.edu/archives/fall-2019/" class="button icon fa-book">2019 Website</a></li>
										</ul>
										<p>In the Fall 2020 semester Anthony co-taught Introduction to Artificial Intelligence with <a href="https://www.biostat.wisc.edu/~yli/">Yin Li</a>, <a href="http://pages.cs.wisc.edu/~yliang/">Yingyu Liang</a>, and <a href="https://daifengwanglab.org/">Daifeng Wang</a>.</p>
										<ul class="actions">
											<li><a href="https://happyharrycn.github.io/CS540-Fall20/" class="button icon fa-book">Course Website</a></li>
										</ul>
										<p>In the Spring 2016-2018 semesters Anthony taught Advanced Bioinformatics.</p>
										<ul class="actions">
											<li><a href="https://www.biostat.wisc.edu/bmi776/spring-18/index.html" class="button icon fa-book">2018 Website</a>
											<a href="https://www.biostat.wisc.edu/bmi776/spring-17/index.html" class="button icon fa-book">2017 Website</a>
											<a href="https://www.biostat.wisc.edu/bmi776/spring-16/index.html" class="button icon fa-book">2016 Website</a></li>
										</ul>
										<p>In the Spring 2015 semester Anthony taught a special topics course on Cancer Bioinformatics.</p>
										<ul class="actions">
											<li><a href="BMI826-S15/index.html" class="button icon fa-book">Course Website</a></li>
										</ul>
